{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889172131,"sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3e4294001G5tWazlwzsTbk5","messageID":"msg_d7b3e3204001AP3Dwn21EO4tP5","sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** pkg/picod  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: \n10: Provide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Valid token allows request\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token in the Authorization header\n22: - **WHEN** a request is made to a PicoD execution endpoint\n23: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL validate the token and allow the request to proceed\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Missing token returns 401\n26: - **GIVEN** a request without an Authorization header\n27: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n28: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Invalid token format returns 401\n31: - **GIVEN** a request with an Authorization header not starting with \"Bearer \"\n32: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n33: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid authorization format\"}`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n36: - **GIVEN** a request with an expired JWT token\n37: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Malformed token returns 401\n41: - **GIVEN** a request with a malformed JWT token\n42: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token malformed\"}`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n46: - **GIVEN** a request with a JWT token signed with wrong key\n47: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token signature invalid\"}`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Token Claims Extraction and Context Propagation\n53: \n54: The system SHALL extract JWT claims and store them in the request context for downstream handlers.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Claims stored in context\n57: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id claim\n58: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n59: - **THEN** the extracted claims SHALL be stored in the request context\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Session ID extracted from token\n62: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n63: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n64: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve session_id from context\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: User ID extracted from token\n67: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with user_id=\"user-456\"\n68: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n69: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve user_id from context\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Sandbox ID extracted from token\n72: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with sandbox_id=\"sandbox-789\"\n73: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n74: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve sandbox_id from context\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Namespace extracted from token\n77: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with namespace=\"default\"\n78: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n79: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve namespace from context\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Multiple claims extracted\n82: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id, user_id, sandbox_id, namespace, and runtime_kind claims\n83: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n84: - **THEN** all claims SHALL be available in the context for downstream use\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Session ID Validation Middleware\n89: \n90: The system SHALL verify that the session_id claim is present and valid.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing session_id returns 403\n93: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token without a session_id claim\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id claim is required\"}`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Empty session_id returns 403\n98: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with empty session_id=\"\"\n99: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n100: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id cannot be empty\"}`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Session ID matches request parameter\n103: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/abc123\n104: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n105: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Session ID mismatch returns 403\n108: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/def456\n109: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n110: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session access denied\"}`\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: Optional Authentication Support\n115: \n116: The system SHALL support optional authentication for specific endpoints.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Optional auth allows anonymous requests\n119: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n120: - **WHEN** a request without a token is made\n121: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed without claims in context\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Optional auth extracts claims when present\n124: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n125: - **WHEN** a request with a valid token is made\n126: - **THEN** the claims SHALL be extracted and stored in context\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Optional auth ignores invalid tokens\n129: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n130: - **WHEN** a request with an invalid token is made\n131: - **THEN** the request SHALL proceed without claims (invalid token is treated as no token)\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: JWT Configuration\n136: \n137: The system SHALL support configurable JWT settings for the PicoD middleware.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Configuration from environment variables\n140: - **GIVEN** environment variables `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER`, `PICOD_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`, and `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY`\n141: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is initialized\n142: - **THEN** the configuration SHALL be populated from these environment variables\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Configuration with public key PEM\n145: - **GIVEN** a valid RSA public key in PEM format in configuration\n146: - **WHEN** the middleware validates tokens\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL use the configured public key to verify signatures\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Configuration with JWKS endpoint\n150: - **GIVEN** a JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) endpoint URL in configuration\n151: - **WHEN** the middleware needs to validate tokens\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL fetch the public key from the JWKS endpoint\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Invalid configuration returns error\n155: - **GIVEN** an invalid JWT configuration (e.g., empty issuer)\n156: - **WHEN** the middleware is initialized\n157: - **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n160: - **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n161: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is loaded\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL use sensible defaults (issuer=\"picod\", expiry=5m)\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Token Refresh Support\n167: \n168: The system SHALL support token refresh for extended sessions.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Refresh token endpoint\n171: - **GIVEN** a valid refresh token\n172: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/auth/refresh` with the refresh token\n173: - **THEN** the server SHALL return a new access token and refresh token pair\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Expired refresh token returns 401\n176: - **GIVEN** an expired refresh token\n177: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n178: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"refresh token expired\"}`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Invalid refresh token returns 401\n181: - **GIVEN** an invalid refresh token\n182: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n183: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid refresh token\"}`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Public Key Endpoint\n188: \n189: The system SHALL expose a public key endpoint for token verification by clients.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Get public key\n192: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with RSA keys\n193: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/.well-known/jwks.json`\n194: - **THEN** the server SHALL return the public key in JWKS format\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Public key includes key ID\n197: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with key versioning\n198: - **WHEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n199: - **THEN** the response SHALL include the key ID (kid) for each key\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Public key algorithm specified\n202: - **GIVEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n203: - **WHEN** the response is returned\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL include the algorithm (alg: RS256) and key type (kty: RSA)\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n209: \n210: The system SHALL expose metrics for JWT middleware operations.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Token validation counter\n213: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n214: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validations_total` counter with labels for result (success/failure)\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Token validation latency\n218: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n219: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n220: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validation_duration_seconds` histogram\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Active session tracking\n223: - **GIVEN** tokens are being validated\n224: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_active_sessions` gauge with session_id labels\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Logging\n230: \n231: The system SHALL implement structured logging for JWT middleware operations.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Successful authentication logged\n234: - **GIVEN** a request with valid token is processed\n235: - **WHEN** authentication succeeds\n236: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, user_id, endpoint, duration\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Failed authentication logged\n239: - **GIVEN** a request with invalid token is processed\n240: - **WHEN** authentication fails\n241: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: error, error_code, endpoint, remote_addr\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Token refresh logged\n244: - **GIVEN** a token refresh request is processed\n245: - **WHEN** refresh succeeds or fails\n246: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, result, duration\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n251: \n252: The system SHALL provide consistent error responses for authentication failures.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: WWW-Authenticate header on 401\n255: - **GIVEN** an unauthenticated request\n256: - **WHEN** the middleware returns HTTP 401\n257: - **THEN** the response SHALL include `WWW-Authenticate: Bearer` header\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JSON error response format\n260: - **GIVEN** an authentication error occurs\n261: - **WHEN** the error response is sent\n262: - **THEN** it SHALL be JSON with fields: error, message, code (optional)\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Error code classification\n265: - **GIVEN** various authentication failures\n266: - **WHEN** errors are returned\n267: - **THEN** each SHALL have a machine-readable code: TOKEN_EXPIRED, TOKEN_INVALID, TOKEN_MALFORMED, MISSING_CLAIMS\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## File Index\n272: \n273: | Path | Purpose |\n274: |------|---------|\n275: | `pkg/picod/jwt_middleware.go` | JWT authentication middleware implementation |\n276: | `pkg/picod/jwt_config.go` | JWT configuration structures and loading |\n277: | `pkg/picod/jwt_types.go` | JWT types and context keys for PicoD |\n278: | `pkg/picod/jwt_handlers.go` | HTTP handlers for auth endpoints (refresh, JWKS) |\n279: | `pkg/picod/errors.go` | JWT and authentication error definitions |\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## Dependencies\n284: \n285: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n286: |------------|---------|---------|\n287: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token parsing and validation |\n288: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Local | Shared JWT types and utilities |\n289: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n290: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics collection |\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## API Endpoints\n295: \n296: | Method | Path | Auth Required | Description |\n297: |--------|------|---------------|-------------|\n298: | POST | `/execute/{session_id}` | Yes | Execute command in sandbox |\n299: | GET | `/execute/{id}/status` | Yes | Get execution status |\n300: | GET | `/execute/{id}/output` | Yes | Stream execution output |\n301: | DELETE | `/execute/{id}` | Yes | Cancel execution |\n302: | POST | `/auth/refresh` | No | Refresh access token |\n303: | GET | `/.well-known/jwks.json` | No | Get public keys in JWKS format |\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Integration Points\n308: \n309: | Component | Integration |\n310: |-----------|-------------|\n311: | `pkg/router` | Reuses JWTManager for token validation; imports TokenClaims type |\n312: | `pkg/picod/executor.go` | Reads session_id from context to validate execution requests |\n313: | `pkg/store` | May store refresh token metadata for revocation |\n314: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Coordinates JWT configuration across components |\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Notes\n319: \n320: - The PicoD JWT middleware leverages the existing `pkg/router` JWT implementation where possible\n321: - Token claims must include `session_id` for all PicoD execution endpoints\n322: - The middleware supports both mandatory and optional authentication patterns\n323: - Public keys are exposed via JWKS endpoint for external verification\n324: - Metrics are prefixed with `picod_` to distinguish from router metrics\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nProvide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid token allows request","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775889172113,"end":1775889172128}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775889172157,"sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3e46a20011x3fOXBtF0jvnD","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b3e3204001AP3Dwn21EO4tP5","sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":33543,"input":4,"output":76,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":3383,"read":30080}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775889178602,"sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3e5fe8001T61qx766lFNt4u","messageID":"msg_d7b3e46d50011bzW9uBEKUXPbU","sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775889182581,"sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3e673b001HoW2fIWTQ8aUJI","messageID":"msg_d7b3e46d50011bzW9uBEKUXPbU","sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","type":"text","text":"I see the file exists with a different AR content. I'll overwrite it with the new specification for AR-022 (CLI publish command).","time":{"start":1775889182576,"end":1775889182576}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775889315081,"sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3f4689001llUBnAGL5iuTeh","messageID":"msg_d7b3e46d50011bzW9uBEKUXPbU","sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","type":"text","text":" system","time":{"start":1775889315078,"end":1775889315078}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889315147,"sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3e6f74001G62QZDe7ctKoI4","messageID":"msg_d7b3e46d50011bzW9uBEKUXPbU","sessionID":"ses_284c33758ffeCobmCn8oE27dEj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: CLI Publish Command (AR-022)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-022  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n\nProvide the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI to deploy packaged agents to Kubernetes using either AgentRuntime CR (via AgentCubeProvider) or standard Deployment/Service (via KubernetesProvider).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - CLI options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `publish` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube publish` without any options\n- **WHEN** the command parses arguments\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `version` = `None`\n  - `image_url` = `None`\n  - `image_username` = `None`\n  - `image_password` = `None`\n  - `description` = `None`\n  - `region` = `None`\n  - `cloud_provider` = `None`\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `node_port` = `None`\n  - `replicas` = `None`\n  - `namespace` = `None`\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path override\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `-f /path/to/agent` or `--workspace /path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided path\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection - AgentCube\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` to deploy the agent as an AgentRuntime CR\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection - Kubernetes\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` to deploy the agent as a Deployment with NodePort Service\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - metadata validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate workspace metadata before attempting to publish.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Missing agent_metadata.yaml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace exists but contains no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` file\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating the metadata file is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid metadata schema\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file contains invalid fields (e.g., unsupported language, invalid port)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` parses the YAML\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` with details about the invalid fields\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - image preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare a container image before deployment, supporting both local and cloud build modes.\n\n#### Scenario: Local build mode with existing image\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"local\"` in metadata and a local Docker image exists for the agent\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` is called with `image_url`, `image_username`, and `image_password` provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Tag the local image with the provided `image_url`\n  2. Login to the registry using credentials if provided\n  3. Push the image to the registry\n  4. Return the full image URL\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build mode\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"cloud\"` in metadata\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the image URL from metadata or options, skipping local Docker operations\n\n#### Scenario: Missing image_url in local mode\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"local\"` and `image_url` is not provided in options or metadata\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` attempts to prepare the image\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating that `image_url` is required for local build mode\n\n#### Scenario: Docker unavailable in local mode\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"local\"` and Docker daemon is not running\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `False` and `PublishRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - AgentCube provider deployment\n\nThe system SHALL deploy agents as AgentRuntime CRs when using the `agentcube` provider.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube deployment with valid metadata\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and metadata contains valid `agent_name`, `image` (with URL), `port`, and required readiness probe fields\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` with the agent configuration\n  2. Include `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` from metadata or environment in `env_vars`\n  3. Set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n  4. Reference `imagePullSecrets` as `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n  5. Return deployment result with `agent_id`, `status`, and endpoint information\n\n#### Scenario: Missing required URLs for AgentCube\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and metadata lacks both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s` validates prerequisites\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube deployment - CR already exists\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and an AgentRuntime CR with the same name already exists in the namespace\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update (patch) the existing CR with the new configuration\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - Kubernetes provider deployment\n\nThe system SHALL deploy agents as standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service when using the `k8s` provider.\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment with valid metadata\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`, Kubernetes client initializes successfully, and metadata contains valid configuration\n- **WHEN** `_publish_k8s` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` with agent name, image URL, port, entrypoint, replicas, and optional node_port\n  2. Create or patch a Kubernetes Deployment with the specified number of replicas\n  3. Create or patch a NodePort Service\n  4. Call `wait_for_deployment_ready` with timeout of 120 seconds\n  5. Return deployment result with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment with custom node port\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and user specifies `--node-port 30080`\n- **WHEN** the deployment is created\n- **THEN** the NodePort Service SHALL use port 30080 (if available in range 30000-32767)\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment with multiple replicas\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and user specifies `--replicas 3`\n- **WHEN** the Deployment is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a Deployment with 3 replicas\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment readiness timeout\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and the deployment fails to become ready within 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TimeoutError` and record the error status in metadata\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment in custom namespace\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and user specifies `--namespace production`\n- **WHEN** deployment is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the Deployment and Service in the `production` namespace\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - metadata updates\n\nThe system SHALL update the workspace metadata after successful or failed publish operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful publish metadata update\n- **GIVEN** the publish operation completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL write to `agent_metadata.yaml` with:\n  - `agent_id` set to the deployed agent identifier\n  - `agent_endpoint` set to the service URL\n  - `k8s_deployment` containing deployment type (\"AgentRuntime\" or \"Deployment\"), name, and namespace\n  - `version` updated if a new version was specified\n  - `status` set to \"published\"\n\n#### Scenario: Failed publish metadata update\n- **GIVEN** the publish operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is handled\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update metadata with `status` set to \"error\" and include error details\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors gracefully using the `_handle_error` pattern.\n\n#### Scenario: Error with verbose mode\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during publish and `--verbose` is enabled\n- **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Print \"Error publishing agent: {error message}\" in red\n  2. Print the full traceback\n  3. Exit with code 1 via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario: Error without verbose mode\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during publish and `--verbose` is disabled\n- **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Print \"Error publishing agent: {error message}\" in red\n  2. Exit with code 1 via `typer.Exit(1)` without printing traceback\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes client initialization failure\n- **GIVEN** the Kubernetes client fails to initialize (e.g., no kubeconfig, invalid credentials)\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception that is propagated through `_handle_error`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - version management\n\nThe system SHALL support explicit version specification for publishing.\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit version override\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--version v2.0.0`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update metadata with the specified version before deployment\n\n#### Scenario: Version from metadata\n- **GIVEN** the user does not specify `--version` but metadata contains a `version` field\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the version from metadata\n\n#### Scenario: No version specified\n- **GIVEN** neither `--version` option nor metadata `version` field is set\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL proceed without a version tag, using \"latest\" as default for image tagging\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - region and cloud provider support\n\nThe system SHALL support region and cloud provider configuration for cloud build scenarios.\n\n#### Scenario: Region specification\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--region us-east-1`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes in cloud build mode\n- **THEN** the system SHALL include the region in deployment configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud provider specification\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes in cloud build mode\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use cloud provider-specific configuration for image building and deployment\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - description override\n\nThe system SHALL support overriding the agent description at publish time.\n\n#### Scenario: Description from CLI option\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--description \"My production agent\"`\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the provided description, overriding any description in metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Description from metadata\n- **GIVEN** the user does not specify `--description` and metadata contains a description\n- **WHEN** the publish command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the description from metadata\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish command - image registry authentication\n\nThe system SHALL support registry authentication for pushing images.\n\n#### Scenario: Registry authentication with credentials\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `--image-username myuser` and `--image-password mypass`\n- **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL authenticate with the registry using the provided credentials before pushing\n\n#### Scenario: Registry authentication without credentials\n- **GIVEN** no registry credentials are provided\n- **WHEN** the image push is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to push without authentication (relying on existing Docker credentials or public registry)\n\n#### Scenario: Image URL with embedded credentials\n- **GIVEN** the `image_url` contains embedded credentials (e.g., `user:pass@registry.com/image`)\n- **WHEN** the image is prepared for publishing\n- **THEN** the system SHALL extract and use the credentials for registry authentication\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `publish` command definition |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class with publish logic |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` for image operations |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for metadata management |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation for metadata |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML parsing for metadata files |\n| `docker>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image operations |\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes client (optional) |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich text output and progress indicators |\n\n---\n\n## CLI Usage Examples\n\n```bash\n# Publish to AgentCube (default provider)\nagentcube publish -f ./my-agent\n\n# Publish to Kubernetes with custom settings\nagentcube publish -f ./my-agent --provider k8s --replicas 3 --node-port 30080\n\n# Publish with registry authentication\nagentcube publish -f ./my-agent --image-url registry.com/myimage:v1.0 \\\n  --image-username myuser --image-password mypass\n\n# Publish with version override\nagentcube publish -f ./my-agent --version v2.0.0\n\n# Publish to custom namespace\nagentcube publish -f ./my-agent --provider k8s --namespace production\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | Uses metadata created during pack phase |\n| `BuildRuntime` | Uses images built during build phase |\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | Creates/updates AgentRuntime CRs in K8s |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | Creates Deployments and Services in K8s |\n| `DockerService` | Tags and pushes images to registries |\n| `MetadataService` | Loads and updates agent metadata |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The `publish` command requires a packaged workspace with valid `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- For `provider=agentcube`, the metadata must include `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n- For `provider=k8s`, the Kubernetes client must have valid kubeconfig for cluster access\n- Image preparation depends on the `build_mode` specified in metadata (local vs cloud)\n- The command updates metadata with deployment information for use by `invoke` and `status` commands\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775889315084,"end":1775889315144}}}}
